msgid "A clearing account holding the value of goods received but not yet billed; the supplier invoice clears it."
msgstr "A clearing account holding the value of goods received but not yet billed; the supplier invoice clears it."

msgid "A company that designs and builds its own finished products end to end (here, the shop building humanoid robots) rather than making parts to another company's specification."
msgstr "A company that designs and builds its own finished products end to end (here, the shop building humanoid robots) rather than making parts to another company's specification."

msgid "A completed job's output, received into inventory at the job's actual accumulated WIP cost."
msgstr "A completed job's output, received into inventory at the job's actual accumulated WIP cost."

msgid "A consumable is a physical item used to make a part that can be used across multiple jobs"
msgstr "A consumable is a physical item used to make a part that can be used across multiple jobs"

msgid "A contractor is a supplier contact with particular abilities and available hours"
msgstr "A contractor is a supplier contact with particular abilities and available hours"

msgid "A customer is a business or person who buys your parts or services."
msgstr "A customer is a business or person who buys your parts or services."

msgid "A dated window postings fall into (Active or Inactive, not open or closed), opened automatically when needed."
msgstr "A dated window postings fall into (Active or Inactive, not open or closed), opened automatically when needed."

msgid "A depreciation method that charges a fixed percentage of remaining book value each period — heavier early, lighter later."
msgstr "A depreciation method that charges a fixed percentage of remaining book value each period — heavier early, lighter later."

msgid "A depreciation method that charges an equal amount each period across the asset's useful life."
msgstr "A depreciation method that charges an equal amount each period across the asset's useful life."

msgid "A firm customer commitment to deliver; fulfillment status splits across ship and invoice before reaching Completed."
msgstr "A firm customer commitment to deliver; fulfillment status splits across ship and invoice before reaching Completed."

msgid "A firm order to a supplier; status moves through receive and invoice before Completed as goods and bills arrive."
msgstr "A firm order to a supplier; status moves through receive and invoice before Completed as goods and bills arrive."

msgid "A issue record tracks quality issues and their resolution process."
msgstr "A issue record tracks quality issues and their resolution process."

msgid "A Make to Order component that gets its own job and routing inside the parent's build."
msgstr "A Make to Order component that gets its own job and routing inside the parent's build."

msgid "A Make to Order component whose parts are issued together into the parent job — no separate build."
msgstr "A Make to Order component whose parts are issued together into the parent job — no separate build."

msgid "A material is a physical item used to make a part that can be used across multiple jobs"
msgstr "A material is a physical item used to make a part that can be used across multiple jobs"

msgid "A name is required to save a view"
msgstr "A name is required to save a view"

msgid "A new purchase order will be created for each supplier. Alternatively, you can choose an existing draft purchase order for the supplier to add the outside operations to."
msgstr "A new purchase order will be created for each supplier. Alternatively, you can choose an existing draft purchase order for the supplier to add the outside operations to."

msgid "A new revision will be created using a copy of the current revision"
msgstr "A new revision will be created using a copy of the current revision"

msgid "A new size will be created using a copy of the current size"
msgstr "A new size will be created using a copy of the current size"

msgid "A non-taxable surcharge (e.g. recoverable expenses like permit fees) added to the line; excluded from the tax base."
msgstr "A non-taxable surcharge (e.g. recoverable expenses like permit fees) added to the line; excluded from the tax base."

msgid "A nonconformance task that fixes a confirmed root cause — as opposed to a preventive or immediate containment action."
msgstr "A nonconformance task that fixes a confirmed root cause — as opposed to a preventive or immediate containment action."

msgid "A nonconformance task that stops the problem recurring elsewhere — distinct from the corrective fix and containment."
msgstr "A nonconformance task that stops the problem recurring elsewhere — distinct from the corrective fix and containment."

msgid "A part contains the information about a specific item that can be purchased or manufactured."
msgstr "A part contains the information about a specific item that can be purchased or manufactured."

msgid "A posted accounting entry: a header plus balanced debit and credit lines against GL accounts."
msgstr "A posted accounting entry: a header plus balanced debit and credit lines against GL accounts."

msgid "A pre-written description inserted into every issue that uses this workflow; placeholders like {itemId} and {location} are substituted at creation."
msgstr "A pre-written description inserted into every issue that uses this workflow; placeholders like {itemId} and {location} are substituted at creation."

msgid "A priced sales quotation; Draft → Sent → Ordered, or ends Lost, Expired, or Cancelled."
msgstr "A priced sales quotation; Draft → Sent → Ordered, or ends Lost, Expired, or Cancelled."

msgid "A purchase invoice is a document that specifies the products or services purchased by a customer and the corresponding cost."
msgstr "A purchase invoice is a document that specifies the products or services purchased by a customer and the corresponding cost."

msgid "A quality issue — a logged deviation or defect with a configurable workflow of investigation and action tasks."
msgstr "A quality issue — a logged deviation or defect with a configurable workflow of investigation and action tasks."

msgid "A quantity of identical units shares one tracked entity and batch number — one entity, many units."
msgstr "A quantity of identical units shares one tracked entity and batch number — one entity, many units."

msgid "A quote is a set of prices for specific parts and quantities."
msgstr "A quote is a set of prices for specific parts and quantities."

msgid "A quote line contains pricing and lead times for a particular part"
msgstr "A quote line contains pricing and lead times for a particular part"

msgid "A sales invoice (you bill a customer) or purchase invoice (a supplier bills you); payment is a field, not a separate record."
msgstr "A sales invoice (you bill a customer) or purchase invoice (a supplier bills you); payment is a field, not a separate record."

msgid "A sales invoice is a document that specifies the products or services sold to a customer and the corresponding cost."
msgstr "A sales invoice is a document that specifies the products or services sold to a customer and the corresponding cost."

msgid "A sales invoice line contains invoice details for a particular item"
msgstr "A sales invoice line contains invoice details for a particular item"

msgid "A sales order contains information about the agreement between the company and a specific customer for parts and services."
msgstr "A sales order contains information about the agreement between the company and a specific customer for parts and services."

msgid "A sales order line contains order details for a particular item"
msgstr "A sales order line contains order details for a particular item"

msgid "A sales request for quote (RFQ) is a customer inquiry for pricing on a set of parts and quantities. It may result in a quote."
msgstr "A sales request for quote (RFQ) is a customer inquiry for pricing on a set of parts and quantities. It may result in a quote."

msgid "A sales RFQ (a customer asks you to quote) or a purchasing RFQ (you ask suppliers); both feed the opportunity thread."
msgstr "A sales RFQ (a customer asks you to quote) or a purchasing RFQ (you ask suppliers); both feed the opportunity thread."

msgid "A separate schedule for tax reporting when tax rules require a method different from book depreciation."
msgstr "A separate schedule for tax reporting when tax rules require a method different from book depreciation."

msgid "A set of companies under one owner that share group-scoped configuration — the chart of accounts, currencies, and dimensions — so the same accounting setup spans every company in the group."
msgstr "A set of companies under one owner that share group-scoped configuration — the chart of accounts, currencies, and dimensions — so the same accounting setup spans every company in the group."

msgid "A shipment line sent straight from supplier to customer, bypassing your warehouse — set per line, not on the header."
msgstr "A shipment line sent straight from supplier to customer, bypassing your warehouse — set per line, not on the header."

msgid "A supplier's priced response to a purchasing RFQ — one per supplier; Draft → Active when they submit, or Declined."
msgstr "A supplier's priced response to a purchasing RFQ — one per supplier; Draft → Active when they submit, or Declined."

msgid "A taxable surcharge (handling, setup, fuel) added to the line; rolls into the tax base."
msgstr "A taxable surcharge (handling, setup, fuel) added to the line; rolls into the tax base."

msgid "A tool is a physical item used to make a part that can be used across multiple jobs"
msgstr "A tool is a physical item used to make a part that can be used across multiple jobs"

msgid "A user records the expiry date on each batch or serial when the goods are received. Use when suppliers ship lots with different expiry dates."
msgstr "A user records the expiry date on each batch or serial when the goods are received. Use when suppliers ship lots with different expiry dates."

